title: BAFTAs 2017: Duke and Duchess of Cambridge in stitches over Stephen Fry's Danny Dyer joke
text:
BAFTAs 2017: Duke and Duchess of Cambridge in stitches over Stephen Fry's Danny Dyer joke BAFTAs 2017: Duke and Duchess of Cambridge in stitches over Stephen Fry's Danny Dyer joke PRINCE WILLIAM showed he had a sense of humour at the BAFTAs tonight when Stephen Fry made a joke at his expense. PUBLISHED: 22:31, Sun, Feb 12, 2017 | UPDATED: 23:01, Sun, Feb 12, 2017 
Presenting the prestigious awards ceremony, Fry, 59, welcomed William and his wife, the Duchess of Cambridge to the event. 
He said: "We are delighted that Their Royal Highness's the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge are here for this very special evening. 
"We're particularly pleased that the Duchess is here because she will be such a support to her husband. 
"After watching a recent episode of Who Do You Think You Are? he is still recovering from the devastating news he is related to Danny Dyer."
